[00:23.292]How many winters in a gaze,
[00:27.925]Lost inside a maze?
[00:31.094]And how many feelings unspoken,
[00:35.627]Held in this hand?
[00:39.060]The weight of the old skies on my shoulders,
[00:43.791]Sunlight in disguise
[00:46.008]Who would have known
[00:47.591]There's an end to eternity?
[00:53.677]The lone tale is no more
[00:57.277]As a breeze brushes by
[01:01.294]As the days drift on by
[01:05.060]Found a steady shore of trust
[01:09.294]In this vast world
[01:12.976]As we walk side by side
[01:16.859]The script is fading away
[01:20.943]And the frozen dawn streams forth
[01:25.227]Into the new
[01:48.127]Now I can see
[01:51.076]You were always there for me
[01:55.093]Setting my burden down,
[01:57.777]A quiet spring has come
[01:59.724]I am in a brand new chapter
[02:28.243]As a breeze brushes by
[02:32.027]As the days drift on by
[02:36.109]Found a steady shore of trust
[02:40.342]In this vast world
[02:44.092]As we walk side by side
[02:48.275]The script is fading away
[02:52.175]And the frozen dawn streams forth
[02:55.927]The weight of yesterday
[03:00.141]Will never hold me again
[03:03.977]Cause when the tides turn and sway
[03:08.210]We'll know our way
[03:12.026]Don't need to be afraid
[03:15.993]Set sail and row away
[03:19.976]Never felt so safe,
[03:22.646]With you, I can step into the new
